The production cross sections for the identified nuclei
were determined by correcting the measured counting
rates for ion-optical transmission losses in the
spectrometer, losses due to secondary reactions in the
target and materials at the intermediate focal plane,
losses due to non-fully stripped charge states, and the
dead time of the data acquisition system.  Finally, the
corrected rates were normalized to the primary beam
